```json
{"answer":"Regular Users see a simpler Dashboard focused on their own work. The “Check attendance” card allows the user to check in and check out. Typical flow: 1. Go to the Dashboard. 2. Find the “Check attendance” card. 3. Enter your username if requested. 4. Click “Check In” when you start work. 5. Click “Check Out” when you finish. Working hours (for example 09:00–17:00) may be shown on the card.", "citations":[{"rank":1,"id":"AI_Virtual_Office_Guideline.pdf-10","source":"AI_Virtual_Office_Guideline.pdf"}, {"rank":2,"id":"AI_Virtual_Office_Guideline.pdf-3","source":"AI_Virtual_Office_Guideline.pdf"}]}
```

```json
{"answer":"From the Dashboard, open the “User Management” card and follow on-screen controls to view and edit permissions. The exact layout may vary, but the goal is always to control who can access which features. From the Dashboard: 1. Locate the “User Management” card. 2. Click the expand icon OR the “Add New User” button. 3. You will be redirected to the User Management screen.", "citations":[{"rank":1,"id":"AI_Virtual_Office_Guideline.pdf-16","source":"AI_Virtual_Office_Guideline.pdf"}, {"rank":2,"id":"AI_Virtual_Office_Guideline.pdf-11","source":"AI_Virtual_Office_Guideline.pdf"}]}
